1
00:00:16,831 --> 00:00:18,123
[alarm beeps]

2
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:22,211
[theme music playing]

3
00:00:58,706 --> 00:00:59,540
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

4
00:00:59,623 --> 00:01:01,125
CHILDREN WERE FILMED SAFELY
GEN AI WAS USED FOR SOME SCENES

5
00:01:02,793 --> 00:01:04,962
The thing is, the more I like you,

6
00:01:05,671 --> 00:01:07,172
the smaller I become.

7
00:01:07,756 --> 00:01:09,049
You know what I mean?

8
00:01:12,177 --> 00:01:15,389
Tell me, how come I have to bear
the weight of your past too?

9
00:01:19,310 --> 00:01:20,603
I'm sorry.

10
00:01:22,855 --> 00:01:24,899
I'm sorry that I'm not as strong
as you are.

11
00:01:26,358 --> 00:01:29,528
[wistful music playing]

12
00:01:43,626 --> 00:01:46,503
[Si-woo] I never tried
to stop anyone from leaving me.

13
00:01:47,171 --> 00:01:49,882
I always respected their decision.

14
00:01:51,175 --> 00:01:53,594
It was my way of being considerate,

15
00:01:53,677 --> 00:01:56,180
while also protecting my pride.

16
00:02:00,976 --> 00:02:02,937
But I can't do that this time.

17
00:02:08,901 --> 00:02:09,902
[scanner beeps]

18
00:02:13,405 --> 00:02:14,406
[scanner beeps]

19
00:02:21,538 --> 00:02:22,539
[scanner beeps]

20
00:02:36,637 --> 00:02:39,306
No matter how pathetic or broken I become…

21
00:02:41,767 --> 00:02:45,020
I don't want to let this person go.

22
00:02:50,484 --> 00:02:54,530
EPISODE 9
THERE'S AN ERROR, STILL CLOCKING IN!

23
00:02:59,952 --> 00:03:01,829
[wistful music playing]

24
00:04:50,979 --> 00:04:53,941
[sighs] I'm so all over the place.

25
00:04:54,024 --> 00:04:56,110
If I can't process my own feelings…

26
00:04:56,193 --> 00:04:58,112
[inhales deeply] …how can anyone else?

27
00:04:58,195 --> 00:04:59,196
[gasps]

28
00:05:00,781 --> 00:05:02,449
Be careful.

29
00:05:15,796 --> 00:05:18,590
Don't you even resent me after all…

30
00:05:19,383 --> 00:05:22,010
after all the terrible things
I said to you?

31
00:05:28,100 --> 00:05:31,228
Yes, I do.
You said the most hurtful things to me.

32
00:05:31,311 --> 00:05:32,479
And it's not like I'm a saint.

33
00:05:32,563 --> 00:05:34,439
Then why are you following me?

34
00:05:34,523 --> 00:05:37,442
Well, because I like you more
than I resent you.

35
00:05:38,402 --> 00:05:39,945
And to make sure you get home safely.

36
00:05:40,028 --> 00:05:41,530
I'm saying…

37
00:05:43,574 --> 00:05:46,910
I'm not really sure
if I can keep on liking you.

38
00:05:49,538 --> 00:05:50,539
I know.

39
00:05:51,665 --> 00:05:54,710
Besides, I can't promise
something like this won't happen again.

40
00:05:55,377 --> 00:05:57,880
So you're saying something like this
could happen again?

41
00:05:57,963 --> 00:06:00,048
In the same way I can't change my past,

42
00:06:00,132 --> 00:06:03,093
things can happen again
that are out of my control.

43
00:06:03,844 --> 00:06:07,806
Still, I want to prove to you
that there was a good reason for it all.

44
00:06:08,682 --> 00:06:10,601
I don't know

45
00:06:10,684 --> 00:06:13,979
if I'll be able to trust you
no matter what.

46
00:06:17,357 --> 00:06:19,693
Why did you arrive late today?

47
00:06:20,736 --> 00:06:23,906
I was late because Choi Soo-jin's mother
suddenly collapsed.

48
00:06:23,989 --> 00:06:25,866
-Is she all right?
-Yeah.

49
00:06:25,949 --> 00:06:28,869
She recovered shortly
after getting to the hospital.

50
00:06:29,536 --> 00:06:30,537
Whatever the reason,

51
00:06:30,621 --> 00:06:34,333
I'm sorry for leaving you all alone today.

52
00:06:34,416 --> 00:06:35,792
[sighs]

53
00:06:36,418 --> 00:06:37,753
I need some time

54
00:06:38,754 --> 00:06:40,255
to sort out my thoughts.

55
00:06:40,839 --> 00:06:44,801
Whatever you need. I'll keep liking you
in the same way I've always liked you.

56
00:06:44,885 --> 00:06:46,178
Mr. Kang.

57
00:06:51,767 --> 00:06:53,143
Take all the time you need to think.

58
00:06:53,227 --> 00:06:55,520
Just as I promised you before,

59
00:06:55,604 --> 00:06:58,273
I'm not going anywhere.
I'll stay right by your side.

60
00:06:59,149 --> 00:07:02,027
And what if I told you
we should end this anyway?

61
00:07:02,110 --> 00:07:04,154
Then I'll try to do even better.

62
00:07:04,238 --> 00:07:06,990
What if I still told you I can't do this?

63
00:07:07,658 --> 00:07:10,244
Then there's nothing I can do.
I'll just have to give up.

64
00:07:12,746 --> 00:07:14,790
[sighs]

65
00:07:14,873 --> 00:07:16,458
But I won't make it easy for you…

66
00:07:18,460 --> 00:07:21,630
because I plan on liking you
with everything that I have.

67
00:07:26,843 --> 00:07:28,762
I'll stop following you now and head back.

68
00:07:30,264 --> 00:07:32,266
It's cold, so hurry inside.

69
00:07:55,080 --> 00:07:58,000
WE'RE A TEAM

70
00:07:58,083 --> 00:07:59,084
[sighs]

71
00:07:59,167 --> 00:08:00,168
[phone buzzes]

72
00:08:04,965 --> 00:08:06,216
[Si-woo] Good night.

73
00:08:20,522 --> 00:08:22,441
[birds chirping]

74
00:08:23,900 --> 00:08:26,528
[panting]

75
00:08:31,825 --> 00:08:34,953
[pants] Hey, let's stop. Stop.

76
00:08:35,787 --> 00:08:37,581
Stop. [sighs]

77
00:08:37,664 --> 00:08:40,292
That happens for tagging along
when you never run.

78
00:08:41,043 --> 00:08:44,254
Everyone's running nowadays.
I was curious.

79
00:08:44,338 --> 00:08:47,174
But I'm done with this. It's way too hard.

80
00:08:52,512 --> 00:08:55,098
-[exhales]
-[sighs]

81
00:08:56,183 --> 00:08:58,393
It's the weekend.
Aren't you seeing Ji-yoon?

82
00:08:59,686 --> 00:09:00,896
I'm waiting on her.

83
00:09:00,979 --> 00:09:02,022
Sure.

84
00:09:02,856 --> 00:09:05,359
-Everyone's got a date but me.
-[phone buzzes]

85
00:09:08,362 --> 00:09:09,571
[Father] I moved yesterday.

86
00:09:11,865 --> 00:09:13,450
What is it?

87
00:09:13,533 --> 00:09:15,535
Did Ji-yoon say she can't see you today?

88
00:09:16,495 --> 00:09:17,496
It's my father.

89
00:09:18,163 --> 00:09:19,706
He said he moved yesterday.

90
00:09:19,790 --> 00:09:22,376
[Seong-min] Oh, already? [chuckles]

91
00:09:22,459 --> 00:09:25,587
His habit of telling you after the fact
hasn't changed.

92
00:09:27,422 --> 00:09:28,632
Shouldn't you go and visit him?

93
00:09:29,591 --> 00:09:31,843
[sighs] It's not that easy.

94
00:09:31,927 --> 00:09:33,970
Do you still resent your father?

95
00:09:34,054 --> 00:09:36,723
[scoffs] At my age? Please.

96
00:09:36,807 --> 00:09:39,518
Your entire life hit a hard reset
because of him.

97
00:09:40,227 --> 00:09:41,561
You're allowed to resent him a little.

98
00:09:41,645 --> 00:09:43,438
I'm sure that's how I felt back then,

99
00:09:44,231 --> 00:09:45,482
but now?

100
00:09:47,025 --> 00:09:48,151
It's just numb.

101
00:09:48,944 --> 00:09:50,237
It doesn't even hurt

102
00:09:50,987 --> 00:09:52,197
or even itch either.

103
00:09:52,280 --> 00:09:54,825
I think that might be worse though.

104
00:09:55,492 --> 00:09:56,493
Yeah, maybe.

105
00:09:57,536 --> 00:09:59,621
[server] Here's your chicken.

106
00:10:02,040 --> 00:10:04,334
[Seong-min]
You ordering fried chicken? You?

107
00:10:04,418 --> 00:10:05,710
And for lunch, no less?

108
00:10:05,794 --> 00:10:09,297
Ji-yoon said she likes it,
so I thought I'd try it.

109
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:13,718
Of course you went for the chicken breast.

110
00:10:21,226 --> 00:10:23,728
When someone tells you
that they need time,

111
00:10:23,812 --> 00:10:25,230
how much space should you give 'em?

112
00:10:25,313 --> 00:10:27,607
-Is that what Ji-yoon said?
-Mmm.

113
00:10:27,691 --> 00:10:28,692
Oh, wow.

114
00:10:28,775 --> 00:10:31,111
So the time has finally come

115
00:10:31,194 --> 00:10:32,946
where I get to give you some advice.

116
00:10:34,364 --> 00:10:35,574
I'll hear you out at least.

117
00:10:36,908 --> 00:10:38,618
So,

118
00:10:38,702 --> 00:10:40,996
just because she needs time to think,

119
00:10:41,079 --> 00:10:42,622
it doesn't mean
you should leave her alone.

120
00:10:42,706 --> 00:10:45,500
But you can't cling so much
that you get on her nerves either.

121
00:10:45,584 --> 00:10:48,712
Whenever she casually turns around,
you just need to be there,

122
00:10:48,795 --> 00:10:52,007
lingering nearby,
looking a little different from usual,

123
00:10:52,090 --> 00:10:53,133
with soulful eyes.

124
00:10:54,718 --> 00:10:56,720
-Don't stalkers do that?
-Ugh.

125
00:10:56,803 --> 00:10:58,013
You're so dry.

126
00:10:58,096 --> 00:11:01,892
So, you can't completely cut her off
because she needs some time.

127
00:11:01,975 --> 00:11:05,061
You still have to check in
every morning and night.

128
00:11:05,145 --> 00:11:06,897
And end your texts with a question mark.

129
00:11:06,980 --> 00:11:09,524
-Question mark?
-Come on.

130
00:11:09,608 --> 00:11:12,611
I mean, that's the only way
to keep the conversation going.

131
00:11:12,694 --> 00:11:16,364
[sighs] Never mind.
I'll handle it my own way.

132
00:11:16,448 --> 00:11:19,743
-Hold on. I've still got tons to tell you.
-Just eat.

133
00:11:19,826 --> 00:11:21,203
[groans]

134
00:11:26,791 --> 00:11:28,251
Hold on.

135
00:11:29,002 --> 00:11:30,921
Why's everyone gathered there?

136
00:11:31,004 --> 00:11:32,297
[chuckling]

137
00:11:36,676 --> 00:11:37,928
[gasps]

138
00:11:38,011 --> 00:11:39,888
-What are you doing?
-Well, Na-ri said she wanted to brag.

139
00:11:39,971 --> 00:11:42,474
-About what?
-Mr. Kang!

140
00:11:42,557 --> 00:11:44,100
Look at him.

141
00:11:44,184 --> 00:11:46,561
Doesn't Mr. Kang look
totally handsome today?

142
00:11:46,645 --> 00:11:49,314
I mean, he looks super young
with his hair down like that!

143
00:11:49,397 --> 00:11:50,899
His outfit too.

144
00:11:50,982 --> 00:11:53,568
He's rocking that boyfriend look today.
[squeals]

145
00:11:53,652 --> 00:11:55,278
-He looks so handsome.
-He looks younger now.

146
00:11:55,362 --> 00:11:58,448
I'm off now, girls. You can go inside
and continue enjoying the view.

147
00:11:58,532 --> 00:11:59,824
[upbeat music playing]

148
00:11:59,908 --> 00:12:01,451
[sighs]

149
00:12:02,202 --> 00:12:03,203
Huh?

150
00:12:03,286 --> 00:12:06,248
-[chattering]
-Oh. Hey there.

151
00:12:31,189 --> 00:12:34,401
[Seong-min] So, you can't completely
cut her off because she needs some time.

152
00:12:34,484 --> 00:12:37,237
You still have to check in
every morning and night.

153
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:39,406
And end your texts with a question mark.

154
00:12:47,289 --> 00:12:48,290
[computer chimes]

155
00:12:51,543 --> 00:12:52,586
KANG SI-WOO

156
00:12:52,669 --> 00:12:53,795
[Si-woo] Good morning?

157
00:13:04,889 --> 00:13:05,974
[sighs]

158
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:10,520
Yep. Wrong answer.

159
00:13:13,648 --> 00:13:14,649
Ms. Cha.

160
00:13:17,277 --> 00:13:18,862
Got a second?

161
00:13:31,875 --> 00:13:34,169
Why aren't you saying anything
about this photo?

162
00:13:35,337 --> 00:13:36,338
What about it?

163
00:13:37,213 --> 00:13:38,214
Take a good look.

164
00:13:38,298 --> 00:13:40,925
This means Mr. Kang and Ms. Choi Soo-jin
used to be married.

165
00:13:41,009 --> 00:13:42,636
Yeah, and so what?

166
00:13:42,719 --> 00:13:45,013
What does their past
have anything to do with you?

167
00:13:45,096 --> 00:13:47,390
Hey, if this gets out,
the whole company will flip out.

168
00:13:47,474 --> 00:13:49,809
It'll be its biggest scandal yet.

169
00:13:50,685 --> 00:13:51,686
Yeah?

170
00:13:52,312 --> 00:13:53,855
DELETE THIS IMAGE?
YES

171
00:13:55,523 --> 00:13:57,150
Then just pretend you never saw it.

172
00:13:57,901 --> 00:13:58,902
You knew, didn't you?

173
00:13:59,986 --> 00:14:01,029
[sighs]

174
00:14:01,780 --> 00:14:04,366
Hey, how did you find out anyway?

175
00:14:05,075 --> 00:14:06,242
By chance.

176
00:14:06,326 --> 00:14:09,996
If he gets put in a tight spot,
it won't do us any good either.

177
00:14:10,080 --> 00:14:13,708
The demo is right around the corner.
There's no need to stir things up.

178
00:14:24,803 --> 00:14:26,346
Are the brochures ready to go?

179
00:14:26,429 --> 00:14:29,057
There were a few rounds of edits,
and now they're off to print.

180
00:14:29,140 --> 00:14:31,518
-And the living appliances?
-No issues there.

181
00:14:31,601 --> 00:14:33,937
-Are we done with the kitchen appliances?
-Yes.

182
00:14:34,020 --> 00:14:35,480
How's the integration program?

183
00:14:35,563 --> 00:14:37,816
It's completed,
but we're still running tests.

184
00:14:37,899 --> 00:14:41,486
All right, so all that's left
is the most important part of Home-AI.

185
00:14:42,987 --> 00:14:44,948
There's still something left?

186
00:14:46,866 --> 00:14:47,867
Yes. Trust.

187
00:14:47,951 --> 00:14:49,744
[gentle music playing]

188
00:14:49,828 --> 00:14:51,830
Just like it happens between two people,

189
00:14:51,913 --> 00:14:54,999
if there's no foundation of trust
between humans and AI,

190
00:14:55,083 --> 00:14:56,459
then our project is bound to fail.

191
00:14:56,543 --> 00:14:57,711
[sighs]

192
00:14:57,794 --> 00:15:00,422
-Sir, are you talking about security?
-Yes.

193
00:15:00,505 --> 00:15:02,298
What can we do?

194
00:15:02,382 --> 00:15:04,551
There's not much time until the demo.

195
00:15:04,634 --> 00:15:07,303
I've been looking for a security solution
for a pretty long time.

196
00:15:07,387 --> 00:15:11,266
Is that what your secret meetings
with the president have been about?

197
00:15:11,349 --> 00:15:12,350
Yes.

198
00:15:12,434 --> 00:15:15,186
And so, have you found the answer?

199
00:15:15,770 --> 00:15:17,313
I'm still looking for it.

200
00:15:26,823 --> 00:15:27,949
But don't worry.

201
00:15:29,075 --> 00:15:30,744
I'll have it solved before the demo.

202
00:15:32,078 --> 00:15:33,997
All right, everyone.
Let's run our final checks.

203
00:15:34,080 --> 00:15:35,039
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

204
00:15:48,303 --> 00:15:52,891
[high-pitched ringing]

205
00:15:53,975 --> 00:15:56,686
[dramatic music playing]

206
00:16:05,445 --> 00:16:07,155
S W - ENTER PIN
INCORRECT PIN

207
00:16:10,074 --> 00:16:11,493
LONGLIVESAEUM
INCORRECT PIN

208
00:16:12,202 --> 00:16:13,453
[inhales deeply]

209
00:16:17,165 --> 00:16:18,666
Interesting taste he's got there.

210
00:16:26,007 --> 00:16:28,551
Oh. Oh.

211
00:16:33,014 --> 00:16:34,516
[laughs]

212
00:16:35,266 --> 00:16:36,267
We did it, Mr. Kim!

213
00:16:36,351 --> 00:16:38,269
The regulatory sandbox approval
came through!

214
00:16:38,353 --> 00:16:39,521
Really?

215
00:16:39,604 --> 00:16:40,897
Then let's start right away!

216
00:16:40,980 --> 00:16:44,400
If we push hard, we can showcase it
at the task force's demo.

217
00:16:44,484 --> 00:16:45,610
[chuckles]

218
00:16:45,693 --> 00:16:47,070
You can work late tonight, right?

219
00:16:47,654 --> 00:16:49,781
[breathing heavily] Yes.

220
00:16:50,698 --> 00:16:51,699
[both chuckle]

221
00:16:57,914 --> 00:16:59,415
[sighs]

222
00:16:59,499 --> 00:17:00,583
Bad news.

223
00:17:00,667 --> 00:17:03,419
I just got hit with overtime,
so I have to cancel tonight.

224
00:17:03,503 --> 00:17:04,587
Sorry.

225
00:17:05,922 --> 00:17:09,050
He must have been so excited
for our first date.

226
00:17:10,009 --> 00:17:12,220
[Jae-in] You can't go on a date
because of work?

227
00:17:12,303 --> 00:17:13,429
[sighs]

228
00:17:14,222 --> 00:17:16,432
-That's super cool.
-[chuckles]

229
00:17:16,516 --> 00:17:18,351
The things you find cool…

230
00:17:18,935 --> 00:17:20,645
I'll call you after I'm done.

231
00:17:21,771 --> 00:17:24,482
-[Jae-in] Okay. You got this, No-ah.
-[chuckles]

232
00:17:28,236 --> 00:17:30,280
[mysterious music playing]

233
00:17:47,797 --> 00:17:48,798
[groans]

234
00:17:48,882 --> 00:17:50,508
[whispers] What's wrong?

235
00:17:50,592 --> 00:17:53,177
Never mind AI.
My honor is completely shattered.

236
00:17:53,261 --> 00:17:56,973
[gasps] Your loan interest?
You haven't taken care of that yet?

237
00:17:57,056 --> 00:18:00,101
[groans]
This is way more complicated than that.

238
00:18:02,145 --> 00:18:04,397
Oh, no. What on earth have I done?

239
00:18:13,114 --> 00:18:15,283
-Are you clocking out?
-Yes.

240
00:18:16,576 --> 00:18:18,536
-How about you?
-[elevator dings]

241
00:18:24,208 --> 00:18:25,209
Come in.

242
00:18:40,516 --> 00:18:42,060
Where are you going?

243
00:18:42,143 --> 00:18:44,103
Well, I'm just going to see you off.

244
00:18:45,188 --> 00:18:47,565
[gentle music playing]

245
00:18:47,649 --> 00:18:49,317
Don't worry.

246
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:51,319
I'm only walking you to the first floor.

247
00:18:51,903 --> 00:18:54,072
You really don't have to try this hard.

248
00:18:54,948 --> 00:18:57,200
Thing is, I can't change the past,

249
00:18:57,283 --> 00:18:58,952
but I can change the present, can't I?

250
00:19:00,620 --> 00:19:05,124
I'll keep trying everything I can
until you can trust me.

251
00:19:09,629 --> 00:19:11,089
[water running]

252
00:19:11,172 --> 00:19:14,801
You know, it's your leg that's broken,
so why are you making me wash your hair?

253
00:19:15,635 --> 00:19:18,304
Of all things, now I'm waiting
on my husband hand and foot.

254
00:19:18,388 --> 00:19:19,639
Unbelievable.

255
00:19:19,722 --> 00:19:21,057
What are you doing?

256
00:19:21,140 --> 00:19:22,433
[Yeong-mook] Hey, sweetheart.

257
00:19:23,893 --> 00:19:25,937
-[water stops]
-[Hye-gyeong groans]

258
00:19:27,021 --> 00:19:29,482
Can you dry your dad's hair? Thank you.

259
00:19:31,025 --> 00:19:32,527
[chuckles]

260
00:19:33,528 --> 00:19:35,989
Come on.
You can't even wash your own hair?

261
00:19:38,866 --> 00:19:40,576
Well, I could if I wanted.

262
00:19:41,828 --> 00:19:42,829
Then why?

263
00:19:44,038 --> 00:19:45,748
[whispers] 'Cause I'm just milking it.

264
00:19:45,832 --> 00:19:47,333
[chuckles] Having fun?

265
00:19:48,084 --> 00:19:51,421
-So much fun. [chuckles]
-[laughing]

266
00:19:52,171 --> 00:19:55,842
-Stop peeling. It's too much work.
-Mmm. Exactly.

267
00:19:55,925 --> 00:19:58,594
You should've just bought
the prepped ones to begin with.

268
00:19:58,678 --> 00:20:00,805
They don't measure up.
They're wilted and not enough.

269
00:20:01,389 --> 00:20:05,476
So, did you choose Dad
because he measured up from day one?

270
00:20:05,560 --> 00:20:07,437
[clearing throat]

271
00:20:12,442 --> 00:20:14,360
Where did it go?

272
00:20:14,444 --> 00:20:16,612
I swear it was around here somewhere.

273
00:20:20,033 --> 00:20:21,200
Well, of course.

274
00:20:21,284 --> 00:20:23,911
Back then,
no other man could compare to your dad.

275
00:20:23,995 --> 00:20:26,539
Really? What did you like about him, huh?

276
00:20:26,622 --> 00:20:29,751
He always kept his word
and didn't make empty promises.

277
00:20:29,834 --> 00:20:31,335
You think that's easy to do?

278
00:20:31,419 --> 00:20:33,546
I just knew that
he was someone I could trust.

279
00:20:37,216 --> 00:20:38,217
I see.

280
00:20:38,926 --> 00:20:39,927
And now?

281
00:20:40,011 --> 00:20:43,890
[whispers] There's no keeping his word.
He won't say anything at all now.

282
00:20:43,973 --> 00:20:46,309
[chuckles] Come on, Mom.
Just give him a little time.

283
00:20:46,392 --> 00:20:48,102
Then I'll grow old just waiting.

284
00:20:48,686 --> 00:20:51,814
I was washing his hair earlier,
and there were so many gray patches.

285
00:20:52,690 --> 00:20:54,609
When did he get so old?

286
00:20:55,401 --> 00:20:58,446
Don't let your precious years
just slip by either, okay?

287
00:20:59,363 --> 00:21:00,364
Mmm.

288
00:21:04,577 --> 00:21:05,620
So, Mom,

289
00:21:07,538 --> 00:21:09,707
what kind of man
do you want me to be with?

290
00:21:09,791 --> 00:21:11,501
Well, as your mother,

291
00:21:12,752 --> 00:21:15,838
I just want someone who will put up
with you, no matter the attitude.

292
00:21:15,922 --> 00:21:18,091
Oh, when do I ever have an attitude?

293
00:21:18,174 --> 00:21:21,260
I just mean I hope that it's someone
who loves you that much.

294
00:21:21,844 --> 00:21:25,765
It should be overflowing,
so it's okay even if it spills a little.

295
00:21:29,602 --> 00:21:31,604
[Si-woo]
Take all the time you need to think.

296
00:21:31,687 --> 00:21:34,941
I'll keep liking you in the same way
I've always liked you.

297
00:21:40,863 --> 00:21:42,782
Seriously, I told you not to come out.

298
00:21:42,865 --> 00:21:45,284
I need to keep moving
so that it heals faster.

299
00:21:45,368 --> 00:21:47,411
I'll just go this far. [chuckles]

300
00:21:48,037 --> 00:21:49,163
Dad?

301
00:21:49,247 --> 00:21:50,248
Mmm?

302
00:21:50,832 --> 00:21:53,209
About the guy
who fixed my cassette player…

303
00:21:53,918 --> 00:21:57,046
-What is he like?
-Why? It's not working?

304
00:21:57,130 --> 00:21:59,549
No. I'm just grateful.

305
00:22:00,758 --> 00:22:04,470
He fixed my stuff so well,
and he keeps you company sometimes.

306
00:22:04,554 --> 00:22:06,472
-You even said he bought you a gift.
-[chuckles]

307
00:22:07,515 --> 00:22:08,933
He's a good kid.

308
00:22:10,309 --> 00:22:11,853
And also a lonely one.

309
00:22:13,312 --> 00:22:14,814
Why?

310
00:22:14,897 --> 00:22:18,025
See how your mother took the time
to wash my hair for me?

311
00:22:18,943 --> 00:22:21,863
No matter how pathetic or broken you are,

312
00:22:21,946 --> 00:22:24,615
in the end,
it's your family that sticks by your side.

313
00:22:26,075 --> 00:22:27,577
But that kid?

314
00:22:28,786 --> 00:22:30,037
He's all alone.

315
00:22:30,121 --> 00:22:34,125
I don't know the exact details,
but his mother passed away,

316
00:22:34,208 --> 00:22:36,752
and he barely sees his father.

317
00:22:38,296 --> 00:22:40,256
I think he's even been divorced once.

318
00:22:41,591 --> 00:22:43,509
-That's rough.
-[chuckles]

319
00:22:44,427 --> 00:22:47,346
But still, he's a really solid guy.

320
00:22:47,889 --> 00:22:50,349
He's grown into a fine man.

321
00:22:51,601 --> 00:22:55,980
His parents would feel so proud
if they could see him now.

322
00:22:56,063 --> 00:22:57,064
[chuckles]

323
00:22:58,733 --> 00:23:01,444
What would you think
if I dated someone like him?

324
00:23:03,196 --> 00:23:04,197
Hmm?

325
00:23:05,489 --> 00:23:06,616
You heard what I said.

326
00:23:10,119 --> 00:23:11,829
[sighs] I don't know.

327
00:23:11,913 --> 00:23:14,832
You said he's a good guy. Why hesitate?

328
00:23:14,916 --> 00:23:16,417
That's a different story.

329
00:23:18,294 --> 00:23:22,006
No matter how great a guy you bring home,
in my eyes, you'll always be too good.

330
00:23:22,089 --> 00:23:24,550
-[chuckles]
-[chuckles] Silly girl.

331
00:23:24,634 --> 00:23:26,677
Just go back inside now. Mom's waiting.

332
00:23:26,761 --> 00:23:28,888
Ah, right. I can't have your mom worrying.

333
00:23:28,971 --> 00:23:29,972
Get home safe.

334
00:23:30,056 --> 00:23:31,682
-Bye, Dad.
-Mm-hmm.

335
00:23:34,435 --> 00:23:35,645
[sighs]

336
00:23:35,728 --> 00:23:38,105
Mr. Jeon? You've been working until now?

337
00:23:38,189 --> 00:23:41,192
-Working and a whole lot of thinking.
-Thinking about what?

338
00:23:45,363 --> 00:23:48,115
Is Ji-yoon seeing anyone right now?

339
00:23:48,199 --> 00:23:49,492
[chuckles] Why?

340
00:23:50,076 --> 00:23:53,746
[sighs] I'm almost certain
it's somebody I know.

341
00:23:55,039 --> 00:23:57,667
What? Hey, hey, hey. What? What? Whoa.

342
00:23:58,292 --> 00:24:01,921
-How did you know?
-Well, they both have matching stickers.

343
00:24:02,004 --> 00:24:03,381
[sighs]

344
00:24:03,464 --> 00:24:04,590
You knew too?

345
00:24:05,216 --> 00:24:08,010
I told her to be careful. Of course.

346
00:24:08,594 --> 00:24:09,679
-Ow!
-You let on that you knew!

347
00:24:09,762 --> 00:24:11,931
I did not. [breathes shakily]

348
00:24:12,014 --> 00:24:13,307
But you see,

349
00:24:13,391 --> 00:24:15,977
I think I made a mistake,
and now things are tense between them.

350
00:24:16,060 --> 00:24:17,061
What should I do?

351
00:24:17,144 --> 00:24:20,231
-And what kind of mistake?
-I can't tell you that.

352
00:24:20,815 --> 00:24:23,025
[sighs] I don't know,
but at times like these…

353
00:24:23,109 --> 00:24:24,902
I should apologize first?

354
00:24:24,986 --> 00:24:27,280
Well, no. Just pretend you don't know.

355
00:24:27,363 --> 00:24:28,489
Huh?

356
00:24:28,572 --> 00:24:31,701
If she realizes you've caught on,
things could get worse.

357
00:24:31,784 --> 00:24:33,327
Just let them deal with their own issues.

358
00:24:34,745 --> 00:24:35,746
Oh.

359
00:24:36,956 --> 00:24:39,041
-You sure?
-Yes. Let's go.

360
00:24:40,835 --> 00:24:41,836
[sighs]

361
00:24:42,545 --> 00:24:44,380
You guys lied to me.
Well, not exactly lied.

362
00:24:44,463 --> 00:24:46,132
-[Jae-in] No-ah!
-[chuckles]

363
00:24:50,761 --> 00:24:51,804
[nervous chuckle]

364
00:24:51,887 --> 00:24:54,557
-Who's this?
-He's my… younger cousin.

365
00:24:57,393 --> 00:24:59,812
Yeah. [chuckles]

366
00:25:00,438 --> 00:25:01,856
It's late. I'll get going.

367
00:25:02,440 --> 00:25:03,441
Good night.

368
00:25:08,529 --> 00:25:11,157
How long have you been waiting for me?

369
00:25:11,240 --> 00:25:13,659
You should have let me know you were here.

370
00:25:13,743 --> 00:25:15,036
"Younger cousin"?

371
00:25:16,245 --> 00:25:17,788
Are you embarrassed about dating me?

372
00:25:17,872 --> 00:25:20,082
I'm not. It's just that…

373
00:25:21,500 --> 00:25:24,045
talking about personal life at work
can get messy.

374
00:25:26,255 --> 00:25:27,381
I'm sorry.

375
00:25:28,215 --> 00:25:30,593
I tend to keep things to myself.

376
00:25:32,011 --> 00:25:34,347
Hey, I know I was wrong. Hmm?

377
00:25:34,430 --> 00:25:36,349
[synth-pop music playing]

378
00:25:36,432 --> 00:25:39,894
One iced Americano
and one hot café latte, please.

379
00:25:40,561 --> 00:25:41,562
It's on me.

380
00:25:41,645 --> 00:25:43,898
Oh, come on. You're a student.

381
00:25:43,981 --> 00:25:46,108
A slice of cheesecake as well, please.

382
00:25:51,280 --> 00:25:52,782
Ahh!

383
00:25:54,867 --> 00:25:56,452
Oh, you got some here.

384
00:25:57,995 --> 00:25:58,996
One moment, please.

385
00:26:06,670 --> 00:26:08,881
We could have stopped by your place first.

386
00:26:08,964 --> 00:26:11,801
-Why? So you can pay for the cab too?
-Well, of course.

387
00:26:11,884 --> 00:26:13,886
-No-ah.
-Hmm?

388
00:26:18,140 --> 00:26:19,433
Don't treat me like a child.

389
00:26:20,059 --> 00:26:21,060
What?

390
00:26:44,208 --> 00:26:45,793
You wouldn't do this with a child.

391
00:26:47,586 --> 00:26:49,755
Hey, I-I never…

392
00:26:49,839 --> 00:26:51,340
I'll call you when I'm home.

393
00:27:23,914 --> 00:27:26,125
GOOD NIGHT

394
00:27:26,208 --> 00:27:28,085
[sighs]

395
00:27:29,462 --> 00:27:30,963
What should I say?

396
00:27:31,046 --> 00:27:33,215
[pop music playing]

397
00:27:34,800 --> 00:27:36,427
MAY I HELP YOU?

398
00:27:38,637 --> 00:27:40,806
I need a good-night message
for my girlfriend

399
00:27:40,890 --> 00:27:43,184
that'll really show her
how much I like her.

400
00:27:43,267 --> 00:27:44,310
In text form.

401
00:27:45,311 --> 00:27:47,104
STAY BY MY SIDE
EVEN IN YOUR DREAMS!

402
00:27:47,188 --> 00:27:48,355
SLEEP WELL, MY LOVE

403
00:27:50,107 --> 00:27:53,235
We've lived together long enough,
and you still haven't figured me out?

404
00:28:02,953 --> 00:28:04,288
YOU ARE ALWAYS THE PERSON
I THINK OF AT THE END OF MY DAY.

405
00:28:04,371 --> 00:28:05,581
YOU HAVE NO IDEA WHAT
A PROFOUND GIFT YOU ARE TO ME.

406
00:28:05,664 --> 00:28:07,416
SWEET DREAMS. HAVE A WONDERFUL
START OF THE DAY TOMORROW.

407
00:28:07,500 --> 00:28:08,584
I LOVE YOU SO MUCH, TRULY!

408
00:28:09,502 --> 00:28:11,295
That is seriously the worst.

409
00:28:16,467 --> 00:28:17,468
[phone buzzes]

410
00:28:21,972 --> 00:28:22,973
MANAGER KANG SI-WOO

411
00:28:23,057 --> 00:28:24,850
[Si-woo] I still like you so much today.

412
00:28:24,934 --> 00:28:25,935
Good night.

413
00:28:28,521 --> 00:28:30,147
This is so unlike him.

414
00:28:31,649 --> 00:28:33,275
But I won't make it easy for you…

415
00:28:33,859 --> 00:28:37,196
because I plan on liking you
with everything that I have.

416
00:29:03,180 --> 00:29:05,808
[typing]

417
00:29:05,891 --> 00:29:06,892
[computer chimes]

418
00:29:09,019 --> 00:29:10,062
[Si-woo] Good morning.

419
00:29:16,652 --> 00:29:17,903
[phone buzzes]

420
00:29:22,658 --> 00:29:24,702
MS. CHA JI-YOON. CONFIRMING YOUR
RESERVATION AT "RESTAURANT OZ"

421
00:29:27,580 --> 00:29:29,123
[sighs]

422
00:29:34,545 --> 00:29:37,923
[Ji-yoon] Should I cancel
our restaurant reservation for to--

423
00:29:38,007 --> 00:29:39,300
Yes, President Han.

424
00:29:41,176 --> 00:29:44,305
We'll have to reschedule.
I have a commitment tonight.

425
00:29:47,391 --> 00:29:48,392
Yes.

426
00:29:50,227 --> 00:29:51,520
-[phone chimes]
-[sighs]

427
00:30:03,115 --> 00:30:04,116
[phone buzzes]

428
00:30:09,371 --> 00:30:11,290
[Young-sam]
Why haven't I heard back from you yet?

429
00:30:11,373 --> 00:30:13,667
Are you even working on what I asked?

430
00:30:13,751 --> 00:30:15,210
[tense music playing]

431
00:30:15,294 --> 00:30:17,796
[Kee-tae]
I actually did find out something,

432
00:30:17,880 --> 00:30:21,717
but it's such a personal
and private matter.

433
00:30:30,726 --> 00:30:32,895
[Young-sam] What is it? Spit it out!

434
00:30:35,272 --> 00:30:39,360
[Kee-tae] There's something suspicious
going on between these two.

435
00:31:00,422 --> 00:31:01,882
You damn lunatic!

436
00:31:01,965 --> 00:31:04,718
[comical music playing]

437
00:31:06,095 --> 00:31:09,139
To think he saw me as a man of ambition.

438
00:31:12,643 --> 00:31:15,604
He completely overestimated me.

439
00:31:17,856 --> 00:31:18,857
You see,

440
00:31:20,234 --> 00:31:22,736
I plan on stretching things out

441
00:31:22,820 --> 00:31:24,905
and outlasting everyone at this company.

442
00:31:39,294 --> 00:31:41,004
[sighs]

443
00:31:47,428 --> 00:31:48,887
Here's the salad you ordered.

444
00:31:48,971 --> 00:31:50,556
-Thank you. Enjoy your meal.
-Thank you. Yes.

445
00:31:50,639 --> 00:31:51,640
Thank you.

446
00:31:53,559 --> 00:31:56,395
Sir, we have set reservation times.

447
00:31:56,478 --> 00:31:58,689
I'm sorry, but may I take your order now?

448
00:31:59,565 --> 00:32:02,151
Sure. I'll have the dinner course, please.

449
00:32:02,234 --> 00:32:03,902
[server] Would that be for one person?

450
00:32:06,739 --> 00:32:08,949
No, for two, please.

451
00:32:09,032 --> 00:32:10,117
Certainly, sir.

452
00:32:24,173 --> 00:32:25,174
You came.

453
00:32:26,633 --> 00:32:27,634
Yes.

454
00:32:27,718 --> 00:32:31,013
I looked like someone
with a tragic backstory.

455
00:32:31,096 --> 00:32:32,264
Thank you for saving me.

456
00:32:33,390 --> 00:32:35,058
What would you do if I hadn't come?

457
00:32:35,142 --> 00:32:36,810
I would have eaten alone.

458
00:32:37,686 --> 00:32:41,523
And then I'd keep making reservations
until you showed up.

459
00:32:47,529 --> 00:32:50,699
I came because
there's something I want to ask you.

460
00:32:51,283 --> 00:32:53,702
Ask me anything, and I'll tell you.

461
00:32:53,786 --> 00:32:54,787
So,

462
00:32:55,954 --> 00:32:58,916
can you tell me

463
00:32:58,999 --> 00:33:01,293
why you two got a divorce?

464
00:33:03,504 --> 00:33:05,047
Where would you like me to start?

465
00:33:05,756 --> 00:33:08,342
The very beginning to the end.

466
00:33:09,384 --> 00:33:10,385
All of it.

467
00:33:12,262 --> 00:33:13,305
[server] Excuse me.

468
00:33:21,230 --> 00:33:23,732
How about we eat first?

469
00:33:24,441 --> 00:33:25,859
Sure.

470
00:33:35,828 --> 00:33:36,829
[gentle music playing]

471
00:33:36,912 --> 00:33:40,290
[Si-woo] Our mothers had been
best friends since high school.

472
00:33:40,374 --> 00:33:43,001
We saw each other often
since we were little,

473
00:33:43,085 --> 00:33:46,463
and they frequently joked
about becoming in-laws one day.

474
00:33:46,964 --> 00:33:47,965
Then…

475
00:33:49,341 --> 00:33:51,385
we ended up at the same college

476
00:33:51,468 --> 00:33:52,928
and naturally started dating.

477
00:33:54,972 --> 00:33:56,890
We had a normal relationship,

478
00:33:56,974 --> 00:33:59,768
and like everyone,
we pictured a future together.

479
00:34:00,477 --> 00:34:01,854
So,

480
00:34:01,937 --> 00:34:04,439
is that when you started
considering marriage?

481
00:34:04,523 --> 00:34:05,524
Yes.

482
00:34:06,608 --> 00:34:10,279
We planned to study abroad together,
so we married after graduation.

483
00:34:11,321 --> 00:34:12,322
Oh.

484
00:34:13,866 --> 00:34:17,452
But then my father's business
suddenly went under,

485
00:34:17,536 --> 00:34:19,037
and then my mother became ill,

486
00:34:19,121 --> 00:34:21,623
so I could no longer go anywhere.

487
00:34:21,707 --> 00:34:24,501
And then when she said she'd go alone,

488
00:34:25,085 --> 00:34:26,837
I couldn't bring myself to stop her.

489
00:34:27,421 --> 00:34:28,422
Why not?

490
00:34:29,673 --> 00:34:33,260
If you're married, aren't you supposed
to choose to stay together?

491
00:34:34,469 --> 00:34:37,180
Well, I believed
that was the best decision for us.

492
00:34:39,641 --> 00:34:42,102
So I decided to get a job and make money,

493
00:34:42,185 --> 00:34:45,188
and Soo-jin went to the States to study.

494
00:34:45,772 --> 00:34:47,691
We both got busy,

495
00:34:47,774 --> 00:34:51,778
and living in opposite time zones,
we gradually talked less and less.

496
00:34:54,281 --> 00:34:56,116
Then my mother passed away,

497
00:34:56,199 --> 00:34:58,327
and when Soo-jin came back
to Korea for a bit,

498
00:34:58,410 --> 00:35:01,580
she told me that she wanted a divorce.

499
00:35:03,832 --> 00:35:06,084
It felt like the natural course of events.

500
00:35:06,168 --> 00:35:08,253
I was too drained by my own life

501
00:35:08,337 --> 00:35:10,964
that I had no room left
to tend to the loneliness

502
00:35:11,048 --> 00:35:12,716
she must have been going through.

503
00:35:14,051 --> 00:35:15,761
So I accepted things as they were.

504
00:35:15,844 --> 00:35:19,848
It took less than a year for us
to go from marriage to divorce.

505
00:35:22,559 --> 00:35:24,269
You went through all of that

506
00:35:25,437 --> 00:35:27,940
in a period of just one year?

507
00:35:29,775 --> 00:35:30,776
Yes.

508
00:35:41,078 --> 00:35:42,955
I pictured it so many times.

509
00:35:43,664 --> 00:35:46,333
How and where did these two meet?

510
00:35:46,416 --> 00:35:47,709
Was it love at first sight?

511
00:35:48,752 --> 00:35:50,379
Who fell for the other first?

512
00:35:51,880 --> 00:35:55,050
I'd wonder over and over again.

513
00:35:56,468 --> 00:35:59,304
Who was to blame for the split?

514
00:36:00,597 --> 00:36:03,600
If it was Mr. Kang's fault…

515
00:36:05,686 --> 00:36:08,105
would I be able to handle whatever it was?

516
00:36:10,399 --> 00:36:11,400
But I…

517
00:36:12,693 --> 00:36:16,321
I actually never imagined that you
were going through things like that.

518
00:36:16,905 --> 00:36:20,158
The part of my past
that you find hard to handle

519
00:36:20,242 --> 00:36:22,744
was the emptiest time of my entire life.

520
00:36:23,662 --> 00:36:25,914
But I won't let it hold me back anymore.

521
00:36:27,249 --> 00:36:31,086
So, every moment I spend liking you
feels too precious to waste.

522
00:36:31,837 --> 00:36:34,089
Even now, every single second of this.

523
00:36:35,507 --> 00:36:37,134
Well,

524
00:36:37,217 --> 00:36:40,846
I don't want to repeat
the same mistake again.

525
00:36:42,681 --> 00:36:45,225
I started this
because I had feelings for you,

526
00:36:46,435 --> 00:36:48,478
but those feelings aren't enough now.

527
00:36:51,064 --> 00:36:53,775
If I'm going to be with you,

528
00:36:53,859 --> 00:36:57,195
I want to be sure that I do so
with a heart… that won't waver.

529
00:36:59,740 --> 00:37:01,450
Is that okay?

530
00:37:03,493 --> 00:37:05,579
Yes, absolutely.

531
00:37:39,571 --> 00:37:42,157
[typing]

532
00:37:42,240 --> 00:37:44,284
[computer chimes]

533
00:37:44,367 --> 00:37:45,285
KANG SI-WOO

534
00:37:45,368 --> 00:37:46,369
[Si-woo] Good morning.

535
00:37:52,793 --> 00:37:54,878
[typing]

536
00:37:55,629 --> 00:37:56,713
[computer chimes]

537
00:37:58,590 --> 00:37:59,591
[Ji-yoon] Good morning.

538
00:37:59,674 --> 00:38:01,676
[pop music playing]

539
00:38:16,316 --> 00:38:17,275
SET THE COOKING TIME

540
00:38:28,745 --> 00:38:30,122
STANDARD
MANAGE DETERGENT

541
00:38:30,205 --> 00:38:33,625
My twin boys just won't listen to me.
Tell me, what should I do?

542
00:38:35,127 --> 00:38:36,711
FIRST CHECK WHAT'S GOING ON
AND GIVE THEM YOUR ATTENTION.

543
00:38:36,795 --> 00:38:38,672
Okay, and how do I give them attention?

544
00:38:38,755 --> 00:38:39,756
No.

545
00:38:42,092 --> 00:38:44,052
We can't push this back by even a day.

546
00:38:55,772 --> 00:38:57,274
[music ends]

547
00:39:00,318 --> 00:39:01,319
Oh.

548
00:39:19,880 --> 00:39:20,881
[chuckles]

549
00:39:39,649 --> 00:39:40,650
Where's Mr. Kang?

550
00:39:41,234 --> 00:39:43,320
-He said he was going to the hospital.
-Why?

551
00:39:43,403 --> 00:39:46,239
He's working too hard.
It took a toll on him, I guess.

552
00:39:51,411 --> 00:39:53,496
MANAGER KANG SI-WOO

553
00:39:56,625 --> 00:39:58,293
[classical music playing]

554
00:40:03,256 --> 00:40:04,257
What's wrong?

555
00:40:05,383 --> 00:40:06,384
Hmm?

556
00:40:06,468 --> 00:40:08,220
You look like you have a lot on your mind.

557
00:40:08,303 --> 00:40:09,304
Ah.

558
00:40:11,306 --> 00:40:13,767
Mr. Kang's gone to the hospital.

559
00:40:13,850 --> 00:40:15,101
Just wondering if he's okay.

560
00:40:16,770 --> 00:40:18,605
Have you tried calling him?

561
00:40:19,731 --> 00:40:20,941
No.

562
00:40:21,024 --> 00:40:22,275
Why not? Call him.

563
00:40:22,859 --> 00:40:24,402
I actually asked him

564
00:40:25,153 --> 00:40:27,030
to give me some time
to think things through.

565
00:40:27,113 --> 00:40:28,740
Did something happen?

566
00:40:30,075 --> 00:40:33,078
Thing is,
I've lost all confidence in myself.

567
00:40:33,161 --> 00:40:35,914
[sighs] You also have moments like that?

568
00:40:37,457 --> 00:40:39,417
I thought I was the only one
who lacked confidence.

569
00:40:39,501 --> 00:40:40,794
[scoffs]

570
00:40:42,087 --> 00:40:44,464
An easy relationship doesn't exist.

571
00:40:44,547 --> 00:40:47,425
At least at work,
you get better with experience, you know?

572
00:40:48,134 --> 00:40:50,011
But why does dating have to be so hard?

573
00:40:50,095 --> 00:40:54,557
Well, seeing someone as intelligent as you
become a fool when it comes to dating

574
00:40:54,641 --> 00:40:56,393
is oddly comforting to me, you know?

575
00:40:56,476 --> 00:41:00,397
-I'm a total failure at this. [chuckles]
-[chuckles]

576
00:41:25,213 --> 00:41:26,423
[sighs]

577
00:41:27,841 --> 00:41:29,467
[gentle music playing]

578
00:41:35,890 --> 00:41:36,933
KANG SI-WOO

579
00:41:37,017 --> 00:41:38,601
[Si-woo] Did you enjoy your lunch?

580
00:41:41,980 --> 00:41:43,481
[typing]

581
00:41:43,565 --> 00:41:44,649
[computer chimes]

582
00:41:47,485 --> 00:41:49,487
[Ji-yoon] Are you feeling okay?

583
00:41:49,571 --> 00:41:50,572
[typing]

584
00:41:51,531 --> 00:41:54,451
[Si-woo]
Yes, I feel much better after the IV.

585
00:41:55,869 --> 00:41:58,079
[Ji-yoon] I thought you said
you take good care of yourself.

586
00:41:58,163 --> 00:42:00,248
We can't have our team lead fall sick.

587
00:42:01,875 --> 00:42:04,669
[Si-woo] This is kind of nice,
being sick once in a while.

588
00:42:09,591 --> 00:42:11,217
[Ji-yoon]
Just take care of your health first.

589
00:42:14,304 --> 00:42:16,306
[Si-woo] I even like hearing you nag.

590
00:42:16,389 --> 00:42:18,683
[scoffs, chuckles]

591
00:42:25,774 --> 00:42:27,984
[Na-ri] The brochures are out!

592
00:42:28,902 --> 00:42:30,362
For you, Mr. Kang.

593
00:42:30,445 --> 00:42:32,572
-This one's for you.
-Thank you.

594
00:42:36,409 --> 00:42:38,203
They look really great. Really nice work.

595
00:42:38,870 --> 00:42:40,163
Thank you. [chuckles]

596
00:42:40,830 --> 00:42:41,831
Tomorrow's the big day.

597
00:42:43,166 --> 00:42:45,710
So let's go ahead and showcase
all we've prepped without a hitch.

598
00:42:46,795 --> 00:42:48,338
What do we do about that thing?

599
00:42:48,421 --> 00:42:49,798
What thing?

600
00:42:49,881 --> 00:42:51,174
The Demo Ghost.

601
00:42:51,257 --> 00:42:53,218
-[sighing]
-[chuckles]

602
00:42:53,885 --> 00:42:54,886
"The Demo Ghost"?

603
00:42:54,969 --> 00:42:57,597
Right, you wouldn't know
since you were in the States.

604
00:42:57,680 --> 00:43:00,100
So there's this ghost that ruins demos

605
00:43:00,183 --> 00:43:02,685
even if you've rehearsed them
countless times.

606
00:43:02,769 --> 00:43:05,480
It made the built-in water dispenser
stop dispensing,

607
00:43:05,563 --> 00:43:07,774
caused the voice recognition to go dead

608
00:43:07,857 --> 00:43:10,693
and stopped a robot vacuum
that was running smoothly.

609
00:43:10,777 --> 00:43:12,404
That's the legendary Demo Ghost.

610
00:43:13,154 --> 00:43:14,864
I've never seen it
with my own eyes though.

611
00:43:14,948 --> 00:43:17,033
Errors happen so often during live demos

612
00:43:17,117 --> 00:43:18,910
that we say it's the ghost's doing.

613
00:43:20,370 --> 00:43:23,498
-Should we use a talisman or something?
-Yeah, I am the talisman.

614
00:43:24,124 --> 00:43:26,626
Don't worry.
You can all go home early today.

615
00:43:26,709 --> 00:43:28,336
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

616
00:43:37,554 --> 00:43:39,013
[phone buzzes]

617
00:43:42,600 --> 00:43:44,310
[Si-woo] Get to bed early tonight.

618
00:43:44,394 --> 00:43:47,230
That way, you'll be ready
to deal with the ghost if it shows up.

619
00:43:50,525 --> 00:43:51,526
[Ji-yoon] You too.

620
00:43:59,534 --> 00:44:01,369
For a long time,

621
00:44:01,453 --> 00:44:05,415
we've been creating home appliances
that make people's lives more convenient.

622
00:44:05,498 --> 00:44:07,000
However, today,

623
00:44:07,083 --> 00:44:09,669
that technology evolves to the next level.

624
00:44:09,752 --> 00:44:11,588
Home-AI is here.

625
00:44:11,671 --> 00:44:14,757
Now, we invite you
to experience that future

626
00:44:14,841 --> 00:44:16,634
and see for yourself.

627
00:44:16,718 --> 00:44:18,720
[upbeat music playing]

628
00:44:21,556 --> 00:44:23,183
So now we are going to take a look

629
00:44:23,266 --> 00:44:26,394
at how Home-AI can transform your day

630
00:44:26,478 --> 00:44:29,063
by following a typical busy day in Seoul.

631
00:44:34,027 --> 00:44:37,822
The first thing you do in the morning
is check your schedule and the weather

632
00:44:37,906 --> 00:44:40,325
on the built-in refrigerator screen

633
00:44:40,408 --> 00:44:44,078
to pick an outfit that suits your day
and is appropriate for the weather.

634
00:44:53,630 --> 00:44:55,673
But when you get to work,
you suddenly remember

635
00:44:55,757 --> 00:44:59,719
that you left the induction cooktop on
with a pot still sitting on it.

636
00:44:59,802 --> 00:45:02,180
In the past,
you would have had to go back home,

637
00:45:02,263 --> 00:45:04,349
but now, you can turn it off remotely
from your phone.

638
00:45:04,432 --> 00:45:05,975
COOKTOP
OFF

639
00:45:12,148 --> 00:45:14,234
While you're working at the office,

640
00:45:14,317 --> 00:45:17,403
you might wonder
how your dog is doing alone at home.

641
00:45:17,487 --> 00:45:20,156
So just check the video
your robot vacuum sends you.

642
00:45:20,240 --> 00:45:21,241
It's Sun-shim.

643
00:45:22,909 --> 00:45:25,411
Sure enough,
Sun-shim is napping again today.

644
00:45:27,205 --> 00:45:29,165
[laughing]

645
00:45:36,047 --> 00:45:39,717
After a long day of work, you come home
and start preparing your meal.

646
00:45:39,801 --> 00:45:42,303
Shall we try a new recipe
for dinner tonight?

647
00:45:42,387 --> 00:45:43,513
CHICKEN, STEAK…

648
00:45:43,596 --> 00:45:47,517
You look up a recipe that can be made
with ingredients in your fridge,

649
00:45:47,600 --> 00:45:48,768
send it to the oven,

650
00:45:48,851 --> 00:45:52,105
and then you just pop the prepped
ingredients into the oven, and done.

651
00:46:05,702 --> 00:46:07,495
After having a nice meal,

652
00:46:07,579 --> 00:46:11,499
it's now time to do one of the most
dreaded household chores, the laundry.

653
00:46:17,171 --> 00:46:19,507
Washing machine, open the door.

654
00:46:19,591 --> 00:46:20,883
[chimes]

655
00:46:20,967 --> 00:46:23,970
-[buzzer sounding]
-[appliances chiming]

656
00:46:25,555 --> 00:46:27,056
[ominous music playing]

657
00:46:31,519 --> 00:46:32,937
Oh, would you look at that.

658
00:46:34,814 --> 00:46:37,525
1 SELECTED
FRIDGE

659
00:46:43,156 --> 00:46:44,782
It's the Demo Ghost.

660
00:46:56,210 --> 00:46:57,211
[chuckles]

661
00:47:10,642 --> 00:47:13,269
[murmuring]

662
00:47:26,407 --> 00:47:27,992
What's that punk doing?

663
00:47:35,750 --> 00:47:38,002
The age of Home-AI has arrived.

664
00:47:38,670 --> 00:47:40,755
Devices have become smarter than ever,

665
00:47:40,838 --> 00:47:44,342
learning our preferences, lifestyles,
medical information,

666
00:47:44,425 --> 00:47:46,344
and they can even recognize our voices.

667
00:47:47,178 --> 00:47:49,847
However,
if something like this were to happen,

668
00:47:49,931 --> 00:47:52,517
people would no longer be able
to trust and use Home-AI.

669
00:47:55,603 --> 00:47:57,563
-Mr. Lee Young-hun.
-Sir?

670
00:47:57,647 --> 00:47:59,941
Did you hack the AI system?

671
00:48:00,024 --> 00:48:01,317
Yes.

672
00:48:03,111 --> 00:48:05,613
I hacked it and planted an error program
in the system.

673
00:48:07,407 --> 00:48:10,493
Does that mean personal data
can be leaked too?

674
00:48:10,576 --> 00:48:11,994
Yes,

675
00:48:12,078 --> 00:48:13,955
it is entirely possible.

676
00:48:15,707 --> 00:48:17,917
[attendees murmuring]

677
00:48:18,000 --> 00:48:19,752
What's going on here?

678
00:48:19,836 --> 00:48:22,088
Um, I don't know. I'm not sure.

679
00:48:31,180 --> 00:48:33,975
-Was it Manager Ko and Director Noh?
-Yes.

680
00:48:34,559 --> 00:48:36,853
They told me to do anything
to sabotage the demo.

681
00:48:36,936 --> 00:48:39,856
-And in return?
-Your position, actually.

682
00:48:39,939 --> 00:48:42,400
They promised I'd be
the task force team lead.

683
00:48:43,192 --> 00:48:46,112
They plan to swallow the Future
Home Appliances task force whole.

684
00:48:46,195 --> 00:48:47,405
They said ruining the demo

685
00:48:48,156 --> 00:48:50,116
would put the task force
under the vice president,

686
00:48:50,199 --> 00:48:52,744
and that Mr. Noh would manage it himself.

687
00:48:52,827 --> 00:48:54,454
[scoffs]

688
00:48:57,165 --> 00:48:58,958
That must have been
pretty tempting for you then.

689
00:48:59,041 --> 00:49:00,251
[chuckles]

690
00:49:01,753 --> 00:49:02,754
No, sir.

691
00:49:04,797 --> 00:49:07,258
"May work speak for itself, not politics."

692
00:49:07,341 --> 00:49:10,261
"You must work for yourself.
Don't do it for others."

693
00:49:11,345 --> 00:49:14,557
You see, I have never forgotten
everything I learned from you.

694
00:49:14,640 --> 00:49:16,517
[uplifting music playing]

695
00:49:20,855 --> 00:49:21,856
So…

696
00:49:22,482 --> 00:49:24,442
do what Mr. Noh has asked of you.

697
00:49:24,525 --> 00:49:25,651
Sir?

698
00:49:26,319 --> 00:49:29,405
If you attack the system,
I'll try to defend against it.

699
00:49:30,490 --> 00:49:31,866
[chuckles]

700
00:49:33,993 --> 00:49:38,456
That is exactly why we made security
the top priority of our Home-AI project.

701
00:49:38,539 --> 00:49:40,792
So we built our new security program.

702
00:49:42,168 --> 00:49:43,961
Neo Solution is finally here.

703
00:49:44,045 --> 00:49:46,589
[pop music playing]

704
00:49:51,427 --> 00:49:52,512
RESTORE

705
00:49:55,890 --> 00:49:59,185
Neo Solution
doesn't just neutralize malware.

706
00:49:59,268 --> 00:50:02,021
It uses blockchain technology,
allowing connected devices

707
00:50:02,104 --> 00:50:03,898
to protect each other
from security threats.

708
00:50:04,482 --> 00:50:07,401
If a single device has an issue,
it is automatically isolated,

709
00:50:07,485 --> 00:50:09,946
keeping the rest
of your Home-AI network secure.

710
00:50:10,988 --> 00:50:12,740
Sensitive information
is stored separately,

711
00:50:12,824 --> 00:50:15,743
providing double,
even triple layers of protection,

712
00:50:17,036 --> 00:50:20,331
creating a world tailored
to each user's unique lifestyle.

713
00:50:22,124 --> 00:50:25,837
We have named it
the "Home-AI user experience."

714
00:51:01,205 --> 00:51:04,250
[sighs] Geez.

715
00:51:12,508 --> 00:51:14,802
[sighs] What on earth was all this?

716
00:51:14,886 --> 00:51:18,848
Well, to put it in simple terms,
I was acting as a double agent.

717
00:51:18,931 --> 00:51:20,349
What?

718
00:51:20,433 --> 00:51:22,310
-[thuds]
-Oh, come on!

719
00:51:22,393 --> 00:51:23,394
-Well done!
-[groans]

720
00:51:23,477 --> 00:51:25,938
It's pretty clear
that Lee Young-hun has turned on us.

721
00:51:26,564 --> 00:51:28,733
I know. I picked the wrong guy.

722
00:51:28,816 --> 00:51:31,027
-Uh, for a month.
-[Kee-tae] A month?

723
00:51:31,110 --> 00:51:32,778
I never thought
he'd do something like this.

724
00:51:32,862 --> 00:51:34,196
I'm talking about you.

725
00:51:34,280 --> 00:51:36,657
Geez. Useless idiot.

726
00:51:37,158 --> 00:51:38,159
Get lost.

727
00:51:40,286 --> 00:51:42,288
But-But-- But, Mr. Noh.

728
00:51:43,581 --> 00:51:46,000
-Yes, this looks far neater.
-[alumnus] Choi Soo-jin.

729
00:51:46,083 --> 00:51:47,084
[attendee chattering]

730
00:51:47,168 --> 00:51:48,878
-Jeong Hyeon-u.
-That one looks good, right?

731
00:51:49,378 --> 00:51:50,963
-Thank you.
-Thank you. Shall we go?

732
00:51:51,047 --> 00:51:52,798
That's right, it's me,
your college classmate.

733
00:51:52,882 --> 00:51:56,010
Hey. I heard you went abroad.
I'm surprised to see you here.

734
00:51:56,093 --> 00:51:58,471
And I heard you two got married.

735
00:51:58,554 --> 00:52:01,432
But I didn't know you and Si-woo
worked at the same company.

736
00:52:02,058 --> 00:52:04,852
-You okay working with your husband?
-Well, about that…

737
00:52:04,936 --> 00:52:07,313
Ms. Choi? President Han is asking for you.

738
00:52:07,396 --> 00:52:08,522
Okay.

739
00:52:09,190 --> 00:52:10,232
Let's talk later.

740
00:52:10,316 --> 00:52:12,568
Sure. The three of us should grab a bite.

741
00:52:12,652 --> 00:52:14,695
-[chuckles] See you.
-Yeah.

742
00:52:26,457 --> 00:52:29,418
[chuckles] Talk about a stroke of luck.

743
00:52:31,379 --> 00:52:36,258
Here's to our Future Home Appliances
task force after a successful demo!

744
00:52:36,342 --> 00:52:38,469
-[all] Cheers!
-[lively music playing]

745
00:52:39,095 --> 00:52:41,639
-Oh! Mr. Kang! Over here!
-Oh!

746
00:52:41,722 --> 00:52:44,183
-Another draft beer here, please!
-Coming.

747
00:52:46,519 --> 00:52:49,522
Wait, I thought that you were going
to the dinner with the clients.

748
00:52:49,605 --> 00:52:51,148
I stopped to say hello and left.

749
00:52:51,232 --> 00:52:53,359
I'm sure the Global Sales Team
can take it from there.

750
00:52:53,442 --> 00:52:56,070
But still,
shouldn't you be with them there too?

751
00:52:56,153 --> 00:52:58,322
Well, this is more important to me.

752
00:52:58,406 --> 00:53:00,074
Everyone, you did a great job today.

753
00:53:00,783 --> 00:53:03,035
Mr. Kang, that wasn't cool.

754
00:53:03,119 --> 00:53:07,206
I mean, seriously,
you almost gave us all a heart attack.

755
00:53:07,289 --> 00:53:09,917
It was the only way we'd be able
to fool the other side completely.

756
00:53:10,001 --> 00:53:12,128
-I hope you understand.
-Of course.

757
00:53:14,130 --> 00:53:15,464
Ah, I'm sorry.

758
00:53:16,507 --> 00:53:21,345
Uh, truth is, I got an offer
from Mr. Ko some time ago.

759
00:53:21,429 --> 00:53:24,181
If I handed over some dirt on you,

760
00:53:25,141 --> 00:53:27,351
he'd make me senior associate.

761
00:53:28,019 --> 00:53:30,688
-Really?
-So what is it that you gave him?

762
00:53:32,231 --> 00:53:33,774
A juicy rumor…

763
00:53:35,317 --> 00:53:39,071
about a workplace romance
between Mr. Kang and Mr. Lee.

764
00:53:42,158 --> 00:53:45,536
-Something to get him off my back.
-[chuckling]

765
00:53:45,619 --> 00:53:48,998
-[laughing]
-Oh, my! [giggling]

766
00:53:49,832 --> 00:53:51,834
But to be honest with you all,

767
00:53:52,710 --> 00:53:54,837
I was very much tempted, you know?

768
00:53:55,838 --> 00:53:57,715
I've been an associate for ages,

769
00:53:57,798 --> 00:53:59,800
and I have twins to feed.

770
00:54:01,844 --> 00:54:03,220
[Si-woo] I understand.

771
00:54:03,304 --> 00:54:07,099
The workplace is where your limits
are constantly tested.

772
00:54:08,225 --> 00:54:09,810
But since you didn't give in,

773
00:54:09,894 --> 00:54:12,730
it means you didn't give up on yourself
and kept your integrity.

774
00:54:14,607 --> 00:54:18,235
Oh, my, you really do know
how to talk, Mr. Kang.

775
00:54:21,530 --> 00:54:24,325
Whatever! I…
I guess I love the task force!

776
00:54:24,408 --> 00:54:26,077
To this team, forever!

777
00:54:26,160 --> 00:54:27,745
-Forever!
-Wait!

778
00:54:28,788 --> 00:54:30,206
I'll be going back
to the Development Team.

779
00:54:30,289 --> 00:54:31,332
What?

780
00:54:31,415 --> 00:54:33,751
But I thought you were staying with us
until launch.

781
00:54:33,834 --> 00:54:36,253
Well, my work here on the task force
is finished now.

782
00:54:36,337 --> 00:54:38,422
Hmm. Time to move on
to the next assignment.

783
00:54:38,506 --> 00:54:43,052
This company doesn't give us enough time
to catch our breath, does it?

784
00:54:43,135 --> 00:54:44,553
We get paid, so we work.

785
00:54:44,637 --> 00:54:46,388
[gasps] Mr. Kang!

786
00:54:46,472 --> 00:54:49,892
You're supposed to take our side,
at least for today!

787
00:54:50,935 --> 00:54:53,979
Here's to us, to being a team forever.

788
00:54:55,106 --> 00:54:57,525
[all] Forever!

789
00:55:04,740 --> 00:55:07,326
[chuckles] Have you been waiting long?

790
00:55:07,409 --> 00:55:10,121
No. You're right on time.
Did you have a good day?

791
00:55:10,204 --> 00:55:12,706
Mmm. I got so many compliments.

792
00:55:12,790 --> 00:55:16,210
It's the first time I'm recognized
purely for my own hard work.

793
00:55:16,293 --> 00:55:18,462
At this rate,
you'll be, like, promoted in no time.

794
00:55:18,546 --> 00:55:19,839
No, not even close.

795
00:55:20,548 --> 00:55:23,092
Let's go eat. I'm starving.

796
00:55:25,427 --> 00:55:27,680
-[chuckling]
-No-ah!

797
00:55:32,351 --> 00:55:33,769
[chuckles] Hi.

798
00:55:34,645 --> 00:55:35,646
Who's this?

799
00:55:43,279 --> 00:55:45,614
[upbeat music playing]

800
00:55:45,698 --> 00:55:47,783
-He's my boyfriend.
-Really?

801
00:55:47,867 --> 00:55:50,536
No way. [chuckling]

802
00:55:51,453 --> 00:55:53,664
We're on the way to grab dinner,
so I'll call you later.

803
00:55:53,747 --> 00:55:55,207
Mm-hmm.

804
00:56:00,796 --> 00:56:02,840
Now that they know,
the news is practically out.

805
00:56:02,923 --> 00:56:05,843
-Sure you can handle that?
-Then you better handle this too.

806
00:56:05,926 --> 00:56:08,345
-Hmm?
-I'm Yoon No-ah's boyfriend!

807
00:56:10,723 --> 00:56:12,892
I'm Yoon No-ah's boyfriend!

808
00:56:13,851 --> 00:56:15,144
[whispers] Damn it.

809
00:56:17,188 --> 00:56:18,564
Wait for me, girlfriend!

810
00:56:19,356 --> 00:56:21,108
I really loved this task force.

811
00:56:21,192 --> 00:56:22,693
We all worked so hard.

812
00:56:22,776 --> 00:56:24,153
[chuckles]

813
00:56:24,236 --> 00:56:26,322
-Where's Mr. Kang?
-He already left.

814
00:56:26,405 --> 00:56:27,573
Huh?

815
00:56:27,656 --> 00:56:30,201
You know, he seemed really exhausted.

816
00:56:30,284 --> 00:56:34,079
[Young-hun sighs] He probably
hasn't been sleeping that much.

817
00:56:34,163 --> 00:56:36,248
He was buried
in that security solution for months.

818
00:56:36,332 --> 00:56:37,458
[phone buzzes]

819
00:56:38,125 --> 00:56:39,793
Doesn't Mr. Kang live alone?

820
00:56:39,877 --> 00:56:41,086
[Si-woo] I'm heading home first.

821
00:56:41,170 --> 00:56:43,547
[Kee-tae] Being alone when you're sick
must be so miserable.

822
00:56:45,090 --> 00:56:47,760
Hey, I think I'm going
to head out early too.

823
00:56:47,843 --> 00:56:50,054
-So suddenly?
-Yeah, my mom…

824
00:56:50,137 --> 00:56:52,181
No, I mean, my dad got injured, so…

825
00:56:52,264 --> 00:56:55,184
Hey, listen! If your father's not well,
you should go there now.

826
00:56:55,267 --> 00:56:56,477
Yes.

827
00:56:56,560 --> 00:56:57,895
-I should.
-Huh.

828
00:56:57,978 --> 00:57:00,522
-I'll be in touch, okay?
-Yes, go ahead then.

829
00:57:00,606 --> 00:57:01,649
-All right, then.
-Bye.

830
00:57:01,732 --> 00:57:03,734
-Good night, everyone.
-Yeah, get going.

831
00:57:04,568 --> 00:57:06,946
-She's just leaving like that?
-Her father's injured.

832
00:57:07,029 --> 00:57:08,447
-Come on, let's toast.
-[Young-hun] Oh, right.

833
00:57:16,372 --> 00:57:18,207
[doorbell rings]

834
00:57:22,169 --> 00:57:23,504
Is he not home?

835
00:57:29,802 --> 00:57:31,178
[line ringing]

836
00:57:31,887 --> 00:57:34,098
[phone ringing]

837
00:57:40,396 --> 00:57:42,481
[phone continues ringing]

838
00:57:42,564 --> 00:57:44,316
[doorbell rings]

839
00:57:44,400 --> 00:57:45,526
[phone chimes]

840
00:57:46,694 --> 00:57:47,695
Mr. Kang?

841
00:57:50,155 --> 00:57:51,156
Mr. Kang?

842
00:57:53,367 --> 00:57:54,660
Mr. Kang!

843
00:57:56,704 --> 00:57:59,331
Mr. Kang! Mr. Kang!

844
00:58:02,001 --> 00:58:03,252
Mr. Kang!

845
00:58:06,213 --> 00:58:07,214
Ji-yoon?

846
00:58:10,592 --> 00:58:11,927
[sighs]

847
00:58:12,678 --> 00:58:14,555
-Where were you?
-[coughs]

848
00:58:14,638 --> 00:58:16,598
I was terrified that you passed out.

849
00:58:17,391 --> 00:58:19,476
I think I'll pass out
from you hitting me so hard.

850
00:58:20,894 --> 00:58:22,646
I was so worried.

851
00:58:30,321 --> 00:58:33,824
How could I possibly
give up on someone like you?

852
00:58:34,825 --> 00:58:36,201
[sighs]

853
00:58:37,411 --> 00:58:39,413
[gentle music playing]

854
00:58:46,920 --> 00:58:48,505
Have some tea.

855
00:59:02,394 --> 00:59:05,939
-There's something I'd like to ask you.
-You still have more questions?

856
00:59:07,107 --> 00:59:10,152
Why did you tell me
right from the beginning

857
00:59:11,487 --> 00:59:13,655
that you're Ms. Choi's ex-husband?

858
00:59:16,283 --> 00:59:17,284
I'm not really sure.

859
00:59:19,161 --> 00:59:22,873
Because it's definitely not something
I would normally share.

860
00:59:23,749 --> 00:59:24,833
Maybe it was a system error,

861
00:59:24,917 --> 00:59:28,170
since you're the only variable
that changes me.

862
00:59:30,964 --> 00:59:34,385
I'm not sure why I said it,
but once I fell in love with you,

863
00:59:35,052 --> 00:59:37,429
I figured it was a good thing
I had already told you.

864
00:59:38,305 --> 00:59:39,306
Pathetic, right?

865
00:59:40,724 --> 00:59:41,725
Yes.

866
00:59:43,352 --> 00:59:48,065
Anyway, let's think things through
and own up to them.

867
00:59:50,692 --> 00:59:51,693
Let's do that.

868
00:59:51,777 --> 00:59:55,239
Don't hide things from me,
saying it's for my sake.

869
00:59:55,322 --> 00:59:58,200
-Tell me everything.
-Okay. I'll do that.

870
01:00:00,202 --> 01:00:03,080
Then you can be honest with me.

871
01:00:07,042 --> 01:00:08,335
Wasn't it difficult?

872
01:00:13,090 --> 01:00:15,092
Being alone for such a long time?

873
01:00:16,885 --> 01:00:18,429
Wasn't it painful?

874
01:00:30,023 --> 01:00:31,024
Yes.

875
01:00:33,360 --> 01:00:34,486
It was painful.

876
01:00:38,699 --> 01:00:40,159
[panting]

877
01:00:41,869 --> 01:00:43,871
When my father's business went under

878
01:00:43,954 --> 01:00:46,290
and he left my mother as if to run away…

879
01:01:04,266 --> 01:01:08,395
When Soo-jin left, insisting
that she'd go study abroad by herself…

880
01:01:14,776 --> 01:01:17,946
And even when she
eventually asked for a divorce,

881
01:01:18,030 --> 01:01:20,324
I couldn't bring myself to fight for us.

882
01:01:21,200 --> 01:01:25,370
So I kept telling myself that letting her
go was the considerate thing to do.

883
01:01:25,871 --> 01:01:27,664
But actually,

884
01:01:27,748 --> 01:01:32,377
it was… just my pride,

885
01:01:32,461 --> 01:01:36,465
not wanting to admit
how miserable and lonely I truly was.

886
01:01:37,883 --> 01:01:39,551
Because I…

887
01:01:39,635 --> 01:01:42,596
simply didn't know how
to share my grief back then.

888
01:01:46,016 --> 01:01:47,684
I guess you were even younger

889
01:01:48,852 --> 01:01:50,604
than I am now, back then.

890
01:01:53,357 --> 01:01:55,150
And all alone like that.

891
01:01:56,777 --> 01:01:59,321
How on earth
did you bear all of that pain?

892
01:02:06,745 --> 01:02:09,498
[sighs] I feel so heartbroken

893
01:02:10,624 --> 01:02:12,084
for the past you.

894
01:02:24,179 --> 01:02:25,681
[Si-woo sighs]

895
01:02:26,848 --> 01:02:28,350
[sighs]

896
01:02:28,433 --> 01:02:29,560
You're in trouble.

897
01:02:30,644 --> 01:02:32,771
Once you feel pity, it's game over.

898
01:02:32,854 --> 01:02:37,150
Well, I truly don't care
about your past anymore.

899
01:02:40,112 --> 01:02:42,114
No matter how temperamental

900
01:02:42,823 --> 01:02:44,783
or how romantic you may be.

901
01:02:47,703 --> 01:02:48,704
So,

902
01:02:49,746 --> 01:02:53,041
I'm just going to focus
on my feelings for you right now.

903
01:02:56,795 --> 01:02:58,213
You see?

904
01:02:58,297 --> 01:03:01,258
I told you it wouldn't be easy
to turn down my feelings for you.

905
01:03:01,341 --> 01:03:02,342
[chuckles quietly]

906
01:03:05,721 --> 01:03:07,306
May I take back what I just said?

907
01:03:09,141 --> 01:03:10,142
You may not.

908
01:03:12,394 --> 01:03:16,607
I'll forget my pride, because now,
I won't let you go no matter what.

909
01:03:56,813 --> 01:03:57,856
[sighs]

910
01:04:01,818 --> 01:04:03,528
Do you want to go out for a walk?

911
01:04:03,612 --> 01:04:04,780
What?

912
01:04:04,863 --> 01:04:07,991
Well, I don't want to do it
just to decompress.

913
01:04:11,119 --> 01:04:13,372
-Then…
-Then?

914
01:04:14,206 --> 01:04:15,791
Buy me a steamed bun.

915
01:04:16,375 --> 01:04:18,502
-A steamed bun?
-Yes.

916
01:04:18,585 --> 01:04:21,630
I haven't had
my first steamed bun this year.

917
01:04:22,214 --> 01:04:23,215
[chuckles]

918
01:04:30,347 --> 01:04:31,348
[sighs]

919
01:04:34,184 --> 01:04:37,145
[ominous music playing]

920
01:04:42,317 --> 01:04:43,276
Found it.

921
01:04:44,027 --> 01:04:45,320
[exhales]

922
01:04:47,114 --> 01:04:49,574
[sighs, exhales]

923
01:04:51,743 --> 01:04:55,372
A COLLEGE COUPLE SUCCESS STORY!
YOU TWO HAPPY TO GET MARRIED?

924
01:04:56,206 --> 01:04:59,501
-You should have some too.
-I don't really eat carbs this late.

925
01:04:59,584 --> 01:05:03,338
Fine, fine.
I'll just pig out by myself then.

926
01:05:04,381 --> 01:05:06,800
Your hands are all red.
Give it. I'll hold it.

927
01:05:13,223 --> 01:05:14,641
[hisses]

928
01:05:14,725 --> 01:05:17,144
Oh, that's hot! [chuckles]

929
01:05:17,227 --> 01:05:18,854
-[exhales sharply]
-Hey, Ji-yoon?

930
01:05:19,646 --> 01:05:21,940
Yes? [inhales sharply]

931
01:05:23,108 --> 01:05:24,443
I love you.

932
01:05:24,526 --> 01:05:26,528
[lighthearted music playing]

933
01:05:36,747 --> 01:05:38,832
You're saying that
with a steamed bun in your hands?

934
01:05:38,915 --> 01:05:42,252
I may be holding a bun,
but I really mean it.

935
01:05:46,089 --> 01:05:47,090
I do too.

936
01:05:49,134 --> 01:05:50,135
What was that?

937
01:05:52,471 --> 01:05:53,764
I love you.

938
01:06:02,731 --> 01:06:03,732
[chuckles]

939
01:06:10,572 --> 01:06:11,573
Oh!

940
01:06:12,657 --> 01:06:13,658
It's snowing.

941
01:06:17,537 --> 01:06:19,664
Mr. Kang, it's snowing!

942
01:06:24,753 --> 01:06:27,214
[Si-woo]
At long last, I found my joy again.

943
01:06:27,923 --> 01:06:31,134
May this joy stay safe and sound

944
01:06:31,218 --> 01:06:33,386
for a long time to come.

945
01:06:33,470 --> 01:06:35,806
[music continues]

946
01:06:57,369 --> 01:06:59,788
SPECIAL THANKS TO BAE YU-RAM

947
01:07:21,893 --> 01:07:24,813
WE'RE A TEAM!

948
01:07:28,817 --> 01:07:30,944
[Ji-yoon] Wait, is this a proposal?

949
01:07:31,695 --> 01:07:33,488
I used to think

950
01:07:33,572 --> 01:07:36,324
that marriage was the natural
next step after dating.

951
01:07:36,408 --> 01:07:38,869
So why am I hesitating about it?

952
01:07:39,452 --> 01:07:42,080
[Kee-tae] Fights between
husband and wife are inevitable.

953
01:07:42,163 --> 01:07:44,416
I don't like having things
lying around like that.

954
01:07:44,499 --> 01:07:45,709
[No-ah] What is all this?

955
01:07:45,792 --> 01:07:47,836
[employee]
Those two were actually married?

956
01:07:47,919 --> 01:07:50,463
What if someone
spreads this rumor with ill intent?

957
01:07:50,547 --> 01:07:52,090
What happened?

958
01:07:52,173 --> 01:07:54,509
[Young-sam]
I might not be able to pull you up,

959
01:07:54,593 --> 01:07:56,761
but I sure as hell
can drag you straight to the bottom!

